File: SACP leader Blade Nzimande. JOHANNESBURG - South African Communist Party (SACP) general-secretary Blade Nzimande believes there is a connection between the 2021 July unrest and the torching of Parliament. Nzimande says there is a counter-revolution happening within the ranks of the ANC. READ: Parliament considering alternative venues for SONA, budget Nzimande was delivering a message of support to the ANC during its 110-anniversary rally in Polokwane on Saturday. "We are saying, President Cyril Ramaphosa must give law enforcement a chance to investigate fully the July counter-revolution last year, the torching of our Parliament but as the SACP, we smell a rat," he said. "We are very suspicious that there is a connection between the July 21 offensive and the torching of our Parliament." The SACP believes there is a connection between the 2021 July unrest and the torching of Parliament. General-Secretary Blade Nzimande says there is a counter-revolution happening within the ranks of the ANC. #DStv403 #eNCA pic.twitter.com/ahKk7qX0su